Class AbstractNanoParser<S,T extends java.lang.Enum<T> & HasPattern>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ai.AbstractNanoParser<S,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - data type to hold parsed input. If parent of NanoParser, S = ASTCell
    T - type of input token. If parent of NanoParser, T = NanoTokens
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parser<S,T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NanoParser

    public class AbstractNanoParser<S,T extends java.lang.Enum<T> & HasPattern>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Parser<S,T>
    Abstract Parser for NanoC language. Parent class of NanoParser. Used to handle all helper methods for concrete parser. Begins by taking in a filename and creating a LexicalAnalyzer object to analyze file. It then gets first Token from file. This is used as a buffer token in case any of the expect(Enum) or consume() methods returns a false or an error.
    Author:
    Martin Tice
